        "text": "Le 14:1-57. The Rites and Sacrifices in Cleansing of the Leper.Rites and sacrifices for the cleansing of a leper; the leprosy being healed, and judged so by the priest, who, going without the camp, must take two living clean birds, &c. The manner of it: one to be slain, the other to be let loose,  Leviticus 14:1-9. On the eighth day two male lambs and one ewe lamb, and meat-offering,  Leviticus 14:10-20. If poor,  Leviticus 14:21-32. Of the leprosy of houses, how to be known,  Leviticus 14:33-48. The manner of cleansing them,  Leviticus 14:49-53. A repetition of this and the former chapter,  Leviticus 14:54-57.  No text from Poole on this verse. ",
